Vice President Yemi Osinbajo is currently in a meeting with the South West Governors at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The meeting is coming 24 hours after the national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, said Amotekun was not a threat to national unity. Amotekun, an initiative of Southwest Governors, was first declared illegal last Tuesday by the Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami The South West governors meeting with Osinbajo commenced after the National Economic Council (NEC) meeting presided by the Vice President. The meeting is presently holding at the Conference Hall, Presidential Villa. Osinbajo’s meeting with the governors might not be unconnected to the controversies surrounding the recently launched regional security outfit, Amotekun. Details later…